comments.body:
I attach a intial patch,kindly review.
First I want use the {{fs.du.interval}} to instead of the 600 secs, but I think it's still not good when I do some operations in datanode and the time of stoping dn service will larger more than du interval time. So I define a new configuration property to instead of it in this code.
{code:title=BlockPoolSlice.java|borderStyle=solid}
// Return the cached value if mtime is okay.
      if (mtime > 0 && (Time.now() - mtime < 600000L)) {
        FsDatasetImpl.LOG.info("Cached dfsUsed found for " + currentDir + ": " +
            cachedDfsUsed);
        return cachedDfsUsed;
      }
{code}

Yeah, it would be good to make the hard-coded value configurable. The added test is nice.
Some minors:
1. It is tested the check occurs in the configured interval time. Add another case beyond the interval?
2. Better to use the constant value defined in {{BlockPoolSlice}}:
{code}
+    String DU_CACHE_FILE = "dfsUsed";
{code}
3. Better to use {{StandardCharsets.UTF_8}}
{code}
new OutputStreamWriter(new FileOutputStream(outFile), "UTF-8"))
{code}
